==Demographics==
At the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]] there were 315 people, 101 households, and 70 families living in the CDP.  The population density was 61 people per square mile. There were 140 housing units.

The median household income was $23,929. The per capita income for the CDP was $12,559.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arizona.hometownlocator.com/az/pima/topawa.cfm |publisher=Arizona.hometownlocator.com |access-date=August 24, 2021 |date=2021 |title=Santa Rosa, AZ Profile: Facts & Data}}</ref>

